{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5ca86a1d-30b0-4b85-b597-27446ef2ed49","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nOptions after `--` are forwarded to the platform runner. You'll also need these package references in your test project:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" />\n```\n\n**Key mapping:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|--------|---------------------------|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\nThe `--filter` stays on the `dotnet test` side and is forwarded automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a248a750-e962-4e57-b6b5-08719ef4400d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura`\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` becomes `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n- When using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, filters work the same way, but direct executable invocation uses `--treenode-filter` instead, and you'll need the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package for TRX output and the coverage packages for code coverage reporting.\n- The newer `dotnet test` integration passes platform-specific options after `--`, so you'd chain all the flags together like `dotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" -- --report-trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura --crashdump --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m`.\n- You'll need the corresponding extension packages for each feature: `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for the report, and similar packages for coverage and crash/hang dumps.","outputTokens":1108,"requestId":"8436:F2917:1E6D7F8:21C00C4:6A0ACEB4"},"id":"56d43a5f-25bb-4faa-8e5b-e4f7cb5b58a8","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:33:11.535Z","parentId":"88f52dbb-f2ec-4234-8040-ad4f6da8f481"}
